CAPE TOWN - Young Kuils River school starters eagerly kicked off the first day of their academic career on Wednesday. Approximately 83 grade R learners and 171 grade one learners were registered at the Sarepta Primary School. But school management said that these numbers were likely to rise. Five-year-old Carlisle Le Grange could not wait to start grade R on Wednesday. He eagerly listed all the school items that his parents bought ahead of start of the school year.  His mom, Genevi√®ve Le Grange, also a teacher, said that Carlisle excitingly counted down the days to the school opening.  Nearly 92,000 grade one learners started their school journey on Wednesday.